animals.name: African Elephant
animals.description: The African elephant is the largest land mammal and is known for its large ears, which help to radiate excess heat.

animals.name: Bengal Tiger
animals.description: The Bengal tiger is a tiger from a specific population of the Panthera tigris tigris subspecies that is native to the Indian subcontinent.

animals.name: Blue Whale
animals.description: The blue whale is the largest animal known to have ever existed, reaching lengths of up to 30 meters.

animals.name: Giant Panda
animals.description: Known for its distinct black and white coloring, the giant panda primarily feeds on bamboo and lives in several mountain ranges in central China.

animals.name: King Penguin
animals.description: The king penguin is the second largest species of penguin, inhabiting sub-Antarctic islands.

animals.name: Siberian Husky
animals.description: The Siberian Husky is a medium-sized working dog breed known for its endurance and willingness to work.

animals.name: Red Fox
animals.description: The red fox is known for its bright red coat and bushy tail. It is the largest of the true foxes and one of the most widely distributed members of the order Carnivora.

animals.name: American Bald Eagle
animals.description: The bald eagle is a bird of prey found in North America, and is most recognized as the national bird and symbol of the United States.

animals.name: Komodo Dragon
animals.description: The Komodo dragon is the largest living species of lizard, found in the Indonesian islands of Komodo, Rinca, Flores, and Gili Motang.

animals.name: African Grey Parrot
animals.description: The African grey parrot is particularly noted for its advanced cognitive abilities and its ability to mimic speech.
